1	//! ScholarVault backend entrypoint.
2	//!
3	//! Boots the SQLite pool (WAL mode), runs migrations, builds the Axum router and
4	//! listens on `HOST:PORT`. All real wiring lives in the `backend` library crate so
5	//! integration tests can construct the same router without spawning a process.
6	
7	use std::net::SocketAddr;
